HEADWORD: Unhat
<hw>Un*hat"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>hat</ets>.]</ety> <def>To take off the hat of; to
remove one's hat, especially as a mark of respect.</def> <rj><au>H.
Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

